# Assets Insurance Reinsurance Recoverables Paid Outstanding Claims Gross Amount

## identifier
de8289

## type
float

## definition
This is the value gross of provisions for doubtful debts, as at the relevant date, of reinsurance recoverables in relation to reinsurance contracts for both paid and outstanding claims against the reporting party.
                                                                                                                                                       
Reinsurance recoverables are any amounts due to the reporting party from a reinsurer that arise from the recognition of Outstanding Claims Liabilities in accordance with capital and prudential standards.

## syntax
### xbrl
- balance=debit
- name=Assets.Insurance.ReinsuranceRecoverablesPaidOutstandingClaimsGross.Amount
- classification=baf/bafpo/bafpo3.02.05
- period=instant
